article.headline: S. Dakota State 33, W. Illinois 29
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Kyle Minett rushed for three touchdowns and 143 yards to lead South Dakota State past Western Illinois 33-29 Saturday. Thomas O'Brien connected with Colin Cochart on a scoring pass that secured the win for the Jackrabbits (1-4, 1-2, Missouri Valley). O'Brien finished with 206 passing yards. Tyler Duffy also rushed for a touchdown. Matt Barr threw for 351 yards and four touchdowns for the Leathernecks (4-2, 2-1), including a 46-yarder to Terriun Crump early in the fourth quarter that put Western Illinois ahead 21-14. Barr threw a TD pass to Josh Gabelmann with 4:30 left and completed a 2-point conversion pass to Aaron Muhammad, allowing the Leathernecks to take the lead again, 29-26. SDSU answered with O'Brien's TD pass with 1:36 left in the game. The victory saved the Jackrabbits from an 0-5 start, the worst in program history.
